THIS IS QA GROUP WORK TEST FRAMEWORK FOR EXECUTING OUR TEST PLAN

##### Install Instructions #####

1. Install Docker Desktop: https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop/
    -After install, make sure Docker is running
2. Clone this repository
3. Open terminal to the project root folder and run command
    docker build -t robot-tests .
4. Run command
    docker run --rm robot-tests


To run the tests without Docker using RobotCode extension in VSCode:
1. Install Python 3.13.x
    -https://www.python.org/downloads/release/python-3139/
2. Install VSCode extensions:
    -RobotCode by Daniel Biehl
    -Python by Microsoft
3. Open terminal to the project root folder and run command
    py -3.13 -m venv .venv
4. Install dependencies by running command
    .venv\Scripts\pip install -r requirements.txt
5. Press: 
CTRL+Shift+P
Python: Select Interpreter
.venv (3.13.x)
6. You should now be able to see "run tests" button inside the test file in VSCode and able to run the tests
Note: If encountering an error "File not found", check that your run-tests.sh End of Line Sequence is "LF"
